The issue you're encountering with repeated values in releaseByPlatformsArray is likely caused by how the data is being mapped and processed. Specifically, if the same platform appears multiple times in the release_dates or if there is duplication in the API response, the releaseByPlatformsArray will reflect these duplicates.

Here are potential reasons and solutions:

1. Duplicate Data in API Response

If the release_dates data from the IGDB API contains duplicate platforms or dates, this will lead to duplicate entries in releaseByPlatformsArray. You can filter duplicates by checking if a device-releaseDate combination already exists.

2. Remove Duplicates from releaseByPlatformsArray

You can filter out duplicates after the array has been populated. Use a combination of Set and .map() to ensure that only unique entries are kept.

Here’s a refactor of your code with a deduplication step:

js
const handleReleaseDates = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  if (parsedData.release_dates) {
    // Clean and process release_dates
    parsedData.release_dates = parsedData.release_dates
      .replace(/{|}/g, "")
      .split(",")
      .map((id) => id.trim());

    if (parsedData.release_dates.length > 0) {
      const releaseDateIds = parsedData.release_dates.join(",");

      try {
        const releaseDateResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
          "https://api.igdb.com/v4/release_dates",
          `fields *; where id = (${releaseDateIds});`,
          headerFromApi
        );

        // Extract platform IDs from release dates
        const platformIds = releaseDateResponse.data
          .map((release) => release.platform)
          .join(",");

        const platformResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
          "https://api.igdb.com/v4/platforms",
          `fields *, platform_logo.*; where id = (${platformIds});`,
          headerFromApi
        );

        const platformMap = platformResponse.data.reduce((map, platform) => {
          map[platform.id] = platform;
          return map;
        }, {});

        parsedData.release_dates = releaseDateResponse.data.map((release) => {
          const platform = platformMap[release.platform];
          return {
            ...release,
            platform: platform
              ? {
                  ...platform,
                  logo: platform.platform_logo || null,
                }
              : `Unknown (${release.platform})`,
          };
        });

        // Map to releaseByPlatformsArray and remove duplicates
        let releaseByPlatformsArray = await Promise.all(
          parsedData.release_dates
            .filter((platform) => platform.platform.name && platform.date)
            .map(async (platform) => {
              const deviceId = await getOrCreateDevice(
                platform.platform?.name === "PC (Microsoft Windows)"
                  ? "PC"
                  : platform.platform?.name,
                platform.platform?.slug,
                platform.platform?.logo?.url
              );
              return {
                releaseDate: new Date(platform.date * 1000)
                  .toISOString()
                  .split("T")[0],
                device: deviceId,
              };
            })
        );

        // Remove duplicates based on 'device' and 'releaseDate'
        releaseByPlatformsArray = Array.from(
          new Set(releaseByPlatformsArray.map((item) => JSON.stringify(item)))
        ).map((item) => JSON.parse(item));

        const devicesArray = releaseByPlatformsArray
          .map((platform) => platform.device)
          .filter((device) => device !== undefined);

        return { releaseByPlatformsArray, devicesArray };
      } catch (error) {
        console.error(`Failed to fetch platforms or logos: ${error.message}`);
      }
    } else {
      parsedData.release_dates = [];
    }
  } else {
    parsedData.release_dates = [];
  }
};

Explanation:

  1. Deduplication: After releaseByPlatformsArray is populated, I use Set to eliminate duplicates by converting each object to a string (JSON.stringify(item)), then converting it back to an object.
  2. Filtering: The .filter() on device ensures only defined devices are included.

This should prevent duplicates from appearing in the releaseByPlatformsArray while keeping the logic for fetching platforms and dates intact.

ChatGPT said:

To handle the creation of similar games and return an array of game IDs that will be assigned to gameData.similar_games, you can follow these steps:

  1. Extract Similar Games: Parse the similar_games field in your data.
  2. Check if Similar Game Exists: For each similar game, check if it already exists in the database (Strapi). If not, create a new entry.
  3. Return the Array of Similar Game IDs: Once the games are created or confirmed, return an array of their IDs to include in gameData.similar_games.

Here’s how you can implement this logic in a new handleSimilarGames function:

Function to Handle Similar Games

js
const handleSimilarGames = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  if (parsedData.similar_games) {
    // Remove curly braces and split into an array
    const similarGameIds = parsedData.similar_games
      .replace(/{|}/g, "")
      .split(",")
      .map((id) => id.trim());

    if (similarGameIds.length > 0) {
      try {
        // Fetch details of similar games using IGDB API
        const similarGamesResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
          "https://api.igdb.com/v4/games",
          `fields *; where id = (${similarGameIds.join(",")});`,
          headerFromApi
        );

        // Array to store the IDs of similar games
        const similarGamesArray = [];

        // Process each similar game
        for (const similarGame of similarGamesResponse.data) {
          // Check if the game already exists in Strapi
          const existingGame = await findGameInStrapi(similarGame.id);

          let gameId;
          if (existingGame) {
            // If the game exists, use its ID
            gameId = existingGame.id;
          } else {
            // If the game doesn't exist, create a new entry
            const newGame = {
              title: similarGame.name,
              slug: similarGame.slug,
              description: similarGame.summary || "",
              site_url: similarGame.url || null,
              // Add more fields as needed from the similar game data
            };

            const createdGame = await createGameInStrapi(newGame);
            gameId = createdGame.id;
          }

          // Add the ID of the similar game to the array
          similarGamesArray.push(gameId);
        }

        // Return the array of similar game IDs
        return similarGamesArray;
      } catch (error) {
        console.error(`Failed to handle similar games: ${error.message}`);
        return [];
      }
    }
  }
  return [];
};

Helper Functions

  1. fetchWithRetry: This is a function for retrying API requests.
  2. findGameInStrapi: A helper function to check if a game already exists in Strapi by its IGDB ID.
  3. createGameInStrapi: A function to create a new game entry in Strapi.

Here’s an example of these helper functions:

js
const findGameInStrapi = async (gameId) => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/strapi/games?filters[igdb_id]=${gameId}`);
    const data = await response.json();
    return data.length > 0 ? data[0] : null;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Error fetching game from Strapi: ${error.message}`);
    return null;
  }
};

const createGameInStrapi = async (gameData) => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/strapi/games`, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: {
        "Content-Type": "application/json",
      },
      body: JSON.stringify(gameData),
    });
    const data = await response.json();
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Error creating game in Strapi: ${error.message}`);
    return null;
  }
};

Integrate into Your Loop

Now, you can integrate this handleSimilarGames function into your existing loop where you create the main game data:

js
for (const parsedData of csvData) {
  try {
    // Handle various game data like genres, themes, etc.
    const gameGenres = await handleGenres(parsedData, headerFromApi);
    // ... Other game data processing

    // Handle similar games
    const similarGames = await handleSimilarGames(parsedData, headerFromApi);

    // Create the main game data
    const gameData = {
      title: parsedData.name || null,
      slug: parsedData.slug || null,
      // ... Other game fields
      similar_games: similarGames || [],
    };

    processGameEntry(gameData);
    console.log(`Added entry for to Strapi.`);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Failed to parse file`, error);
  }
}

Explanation:

  • handleSimilarGames: This function parses the similar_games field, fetches the details from IGDB, checks if the game exists in Strapi, and either retrieves the existing game ID or creates a new game.
  • gameData.similar_games: This will now contain the array of similar game IDs which you can send to Strapi along with the rest of the game data.

const processReleaseDates = async (releaseDates) => {
  const releaseDateIds = releaseDates.map((date) => date.id).join(",");
  try {
    const releaseDateResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
      "https://api.igdb.com/v4/release_dates",
      `fields *; where id = (${releaseDateIds});`,
      headerFromApi
    );

    const platformIds = releaseDateResponse.data.map((release) => release.platform).join(",");
    const platformResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
      "https://api.igdb.com/v4/platforms",
      `fields *; where id = (${platformIds});`,
      headerFromApi
    );

    const platformMap = platformResponse.data.reduce((map, platform) => {
      map[platform.id] = platform;
      return map;
    }, {});

    return releaseDateResponse.data.map((release) => ({
      releaseDate: new Date(release.date * 1000).toISOString().split("T")[0],
      device: platformMap[release.platform]?.name || `Unknown (${release.platform})`,
    }));
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Failed to fetch platforms for release dates: ${error.message}`);
    return [];
  }
};

const handleGameModes = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {

    // If game_modes is a string, remove curly braces and split into an array
    if (typeof parsedData.game_modes === "string") {
      parsedData.game_modes = parsedData.game_modes
        .replace(/{|}/g, "") // Remove curly braces
        .split(",")
        .map((id) => id.trim());
    }

    // Check if game_modes is an array with valid entries
    if (Array.isArray(parsedData.game_modes) && parsedData.game_modes.length > 0) {
      const gameModesIds = parsedData.game_modes.join(","); // Join the array into a comma-separated string
      try {
        const gameModeResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
          "https://api.igdb.com/v4/game_modes",
          `fields *; where id = (${gameModesIds});`,
          headerFromApi
        );

        const gameModeMap = gameModeResponse.data.reduce((map, gameMode) => {
          map[gameMode.id] = gameMode;
          return map;
        }, {});

        // Map game mode IDs to their corresponding game mode names or mark as "Unknown"
        parsedData.game_modes = parsedData.game_modes.map(
          (id) => gameModeMap[id] || { name: `Unknown (${id})` }
        );

        // Extract game mode names
        const gameModesArray = parsedData.game_modes
          .filter((gameMode) => gameMode.name) // Filter out any entries without a name

        console.error(`Failed to fetch game modes: ${error.message}`);

    parsedData.game_modes = []; // Set game_modes to an empty array if not present
  }

const handleLanguageSupports = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  if (parsedData.language_supports) {
    // Remove curly braces and split by commas
    if (typeof parsedData.language_supports === "string") {
      parsedData.language_supports = parsedData.language_supports
        .replace(/{|}/g, "")
        .split(",")
        .map((id) => id.trim());
    }

    if (Array.isArray(parsedData.language_supports) && parsedData.language_supports.length > 0) {
      const languageSupportsIds = parsedData.language_supports.join(",");

      try {
        // Fetch language support data
        const languageSupportsResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
          "https://api.igdb.com/v4/language_supports",
          `fields *; where id = (${languageSupportsIds});`,
          headerFromApi
        );

        // Map language support data by ID
        const languageSupportsMap = languageSupportsResponse.data.reduce((map, langSupp) => {
          map[langSupp.id] = langSupp;
          return map;
        }, {});

        // Process each language support and fetch corresponding language details
        for (let i = 0; i < parsedData.language_supports.length; i++) {
          const langSuppId = parsedData.language_supports[i];
          const languageSupport = languageSupportsMap[langSuppId] || `Unknown (${langSuppId})`;

          // Fetch language details if language support exists
          if (languageSupport !== `Unknown (${langSuppId})`) {
            try {
              const languageId = languageSupport.language;
              const languageDetailsResponse = await fetchWithRetry(
                "https://api.igdb.com/v4/languages",
                `fields *; where id = (${languageId});`,
                headerFromApi
              );

              // Assign language details to the support
              languageSupport.language_details = languageDetailsResponse.data;
            } catch (error) {
              console.error(`Failed to fetch language details for language ID ${languageSupport.language}: ${error.message}`);
            }
          }

          // Replace the language support in parsedData
          parsedData.language_supports[i] = languageSupport;
        }

        // Extract unique language names from the language details
        const languageSupportArray = [
          ...new Set(
            parsedData.language_supports.flatMap((support) =>
              support.language_details
                .filter((detail) => detail.name) // Ensure name exists
                .map((detail) => detail.name)
            )
          ),
        ];

        return languageSupportArray; // Return array of unique language names
      } catch (error) {
        console.error(`Failed to fetch language supports: ${error.message}`);
      }
    } else {
      parsedData.language_supports = []; // Initialize empty array if none found
    }
  } else {
    parsedData.language_supports = []; // Initialize empty array if none found
  }
};

// Helper function to handle fetching and processing data
const fetchDataAndProcess = async (url, ids, headerFromApi) => {
  const response = await fetchWithRetry(url, `fields *; where id = (${ids});`, headerFromApi);
  return response.data.reduce((map, item) => {
    map[item.id] = item;
    return map;
  }, {});
};

// Generic function to handle various fields
const handleFieldData = async (parsedData, fieldName, url, headerFromApi) => {
  if (!parsedData[fieldName]) {
    parsedData[fieldName] = []; // Initialize as empty array if not present
    return parsedData[fieldName];
  }

  parsedData[fieldName] = parsedData[fieldName]
    .replace(/{|}/g, "") // Remove curly braces
    .split(",")
    .map(id => id.trim());

  if (parsedData[fieldName].length === 0) {
    return parsedData[fieldName]; // Return empty array if no IDs
  }

  const ids = parsedData[fieldName].join(",");
  try {
    const dataMap = await fetchDataAndProcess(url, ids, headerFromApi);

    parsedData[fieldName] = parsedData[fieldName].map(id => dataMap[id] || `Unknown (${id})`);

    return parsedData[fieldName]
      .filter(item => item.name) // Filter items that have a name
      .map(item => item.name); // Return names
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Failed to fetch data for ${fieldName}: ${error.message}`);
    return [];
  }
};

// Handle involved companies
const handleInvolvedCompanies = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  return handleFieldData(parsedData, 'involved_companies', "https://api.igdb.com/v4/involved_companies", headerFromApi);
};

// Handle franchises
const handleFrenchies = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  return handleFieldData(parsedData, 'franchises', "https://api.igdb.com/v4/franchises", headerFromApi);
};

// Handle external games
const handleExternalGames = async (parsedData, headerFromApi) => {
  return handleFieldData(parsedData, 'external_games', "https://api.igdb.com/v4/external_games", headerFromApi);
};

  1. Centralized Fetching Logic: Created a fetchDataAndProcess helper function to fetch data and map it, which reduces repetition in your code.

  2. Generic Field Handling: Used a single function handleFieldData to handle all types of field data (involved_companies, franchises, external_games). This function checks for data, cleans it, fetches corresponding details, and returns the names.

  3. Error Handling: Improved error messages by specifying which field failed to fetch data.

const normalizeGenres = (csvData) => {
  csvData.forEach((parsedData) => {
    if (parsedData.genres) {
      // Normalize genres to an array
      if (Array.isArray(parsedData.genres)) {
        // Case 1: If genres is already an array, no need to change it
        parsedData.genres = parsedData.genres.map((id) => id.trim());
      } else if (typeof parsedData.genres === "string") {
        // Case 2: If genres is a string formatted like '{31}', process it
        parsedData.genres = parsedData.genres
          .replace(/{|}/g, "")  // Remove curly braces
          .split(",")          // Split by comma
          .map((id) => id.trim()); // Trim whitespace from each ID
      }
    }
  });
};

  const gameFranchies = await handleFrenchies(game, headerFromApi);

  const categoryId = game.category;
  const categoryName = categoryMapping[categoryId];
  const promptGeneratedDescription = await getRewrittenDescription(game?.name, game?.summary);

  return {
    title: game.name || null,
    slug: game.slug || null,
    description: promptGeneratedDescription || null,
    publishedAt: (game.summary && gameReleaseDates?.devicesArray?.length > 0 && gameWebsiteLinks.length > 0 && gameReleaseDates?.releaseByPlatformsArray?.length > 0)
      ? new Date().toISOString()
      : null,
    genres: gameGenres || [],
    game_modes: gameModes || [],
    player_perspective: gamePlayerPerspectives || [],
    themes: gameThemes || [],
    ...(gameFranchies?.length > 0 && { franchises: gameFranchies }),
    game_engines: gameEngines || [],
    alternative_names: gameAlternativeNames || [],
    keywords: gameKeywords || [],
    language_supports: gameLanguageSupports || [],
    external_games: externalGames || [],
    involved_companies: gameInvolvedCompanies || [],
    coverImage: gameCoverImage || null,
    image: gameBackgroundImage || null,
    collections: gameCollections || [],
    platforms: gamePlatforms || [],
    ...(gameScreenShots?.length > 0 && { screenshots: gameScreenShots }),
    videos: gameVideos || [],
    website_links: gameWebsiteLinks || [],
    releaseByPlatforms: {
      release: gameReleaseDates?.releaseByPlatformsArray || [],
    },
    related_games: similarGames || [],
    expansions: expansionGames || [],
    game_category: categoryName || null,
    devices: gameReleaseDates?.devicesArray || [],
    site_url: game.url,
    aggregateRating: game.aggregated_rating || null,
  };
};

// Helper function to find or create the parent game
const findOrCreateParentGame = async (parentGameId) => {
  try {
    const parentGame = await getParentGameById(parentGameId);
    if (!parentGame) {
      console.error(`Parent game with ID: ${parentGameId} not found.`);
      return null;
    }

    const existingParentGame = await checkIfGameExists(parentGame.slug);
    if (existingParentGame.length > 0) {
      return existingParentGame;
    }

    if (parentGame.category === "7" && parentGame.parent_game) {
      const grandParentGame = await findOrCreateParentGame(parentGame.parent_game);
      parentGame.parent_game = grandParentGame ? grandParentGame.id : null;
    }

    return await createParentGame(parentGame);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Failed to find or create parent game: ${error.message}`);
    return null;
  }
};
